{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8414ac71-f08e-443b-b038-3bbfd23cecd7","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the TFM:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run `dotnet restore` and `dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Check for any NuGet packages that need updated versions for .NET 11 compatibility (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"16324688-0ce5-408f-ad8d-11c4b0c5848b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward guidance question — I don't need to search any codebase or run tools. I can answer directly.","outputTokens":273,"requestId":"282A:18853A:15F95B2:189F430:6A0285AB"},"id":"7a965619-b9eb-4425-b1d2-a874ab9991ca","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:43:15.353Z","parentId":"2e120f03-0bbe-4637-a57a-acb3a29b0bbd"}
